<subSubSection id="3796656070D6FF30FF23EFDF8860FDBF" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7F3336EB70D6FF30FF23EFDF8860FDBF" blockId="168.[151,1436,358,634]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FF23EFDF8B44FE66" bold="true" box="[199,335,394,419]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
This species was transferred from 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FD07EFDE896FFE66" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1855" box="[739,868,395,419]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Hypoclinea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FD07EFDE896FFE66" box="[739,868,395,419]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Hypoclinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FC6FEFDE8E32FE66" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1869" box="[907,1081,395,419]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Bothriomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FC6FEFDE8E32FE66" box="[907,1081,395,419]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Bothriomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FB83EFDF8F34FE67" author="Dalla Torre, C. G. de" box="[1127,1343,394,418]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" refId="ref110399" refString="Dalla Torre, C. G. de (1893) Catalogus hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 7 Formicidae (Heterogyna). Leipzig: G. Engelmann, 289 pp." type="book" year="1893">Dalla Torre (1893)</bibRefCitation>
, then to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FF73EFFB8B23FE03" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[151,296,430,454]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FF73EFFB8B23FE03" box="[151,296,430,454]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FEB1EFFB881EFE03" author="Wheeler, W. M." box="[341,533,430,454]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="1 - 142" refId="ref113081" refString="Wheeler, W. M. (1915 b) The ants of the Baltic Amber. Schriften der Physikalisch-okonomischen Gesellschaft zu Konigsberg in Pr., 55 (1914), 1 - 142." type="journal article" year="1915">Wheeler (1915b)</bibRefCitation>
and finally to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FD24EFFB8975FE03" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[704,894,430,454]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Anonychomyrma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FD24EFFB8975FE03" box="[704,894,430,454]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Anonychomyrma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FC48EFFB8E7BFE03" author="Shattuck, S. O." box="[940,1136,430,454]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="13 - 18" refId="ref112320" refString="Shattuck, S. O. (1992 a) Review of the dolichoderine ant genus Iridomyrme x Mayr with descriptions of three new genera (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Journal of the Australian Entomological Society, 31, 13 - 18." type="journal article" year="1992">
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FC48EFFB8E05FE03" authority="Heterick &amp; Shattuck, 2011" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" box="[940,1038,430,454]" genus="Shattuck" pageId="168" pageNumber="170" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">Shattuck</taxonomicName>
(1992a)
</bibRefCitation>
, this final treatment being accepted by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FEC1EF878BD3FE2F" author="Dlussky, G. M." box="[293,472,466,490]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="616 - 627" refId="ref110477" refString="Dlussky, G. M. (1997) Genera of ants from Baltic Amber. Paleontological Journal, 31 (6), 616 - 627." type="journal article" year="1997">Dlussky (1997)</bibRefCitation>
. It should be noted, however, that extant species of 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FBC1EF868EE8FE2E" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1061,1251,467,491]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Anonychomyrma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FBC1EF868EE8FE2E" box="[1061,1251,467,491]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Anonychomyrma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to 
<collectingCountry id="079B767B70D6FF30FF73EFA38B0CFDCB" box="[151,263,502,526]" name="Indonesia" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="079B767B70D6FF30FEF1EFA28BFCFDCB" box="[277,503,502,526]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="079B767B70D6FF30FDE1EFA38867FDCB" box="[517,620,502,526]" name="Australia" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Australia</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingCountry id="079B767B70D6FF30FD32EFA3899FFDCB" box="[726,916,502,526]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FC42EFA38E68FDCB" author="Shattuck, S. O." box="[934,1123,502,526]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="13 - 18" refId="ref112320" refString="Shattuck, S. O. (1992 a) Review of the dolichoderine ant genus Iridomyrme x Mayr with descriptions of three new genera (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Journal of the Australian Entomological Society, 31, 13 - 18." type="journal article" year="1992">
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FC42EFA38E07FDCB" authority="Heterick &amp; Shattuck, 2011" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" box="[934,1036,502,526]" genus="Shattuck" pageId="168" pageNumber="170" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">Shattuck</taxonomicName>
, 1992a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FB95EFA38EB0FDCB" author="Shattuck, S. O." box="[1137,1211,502,526]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="1 - 181" refId="ref112364" refString="Shattuck, S. O. (1992 b) Generic revision of the ant subfamily Dolichoderinae (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Sociobiology, 21, 1 - 181." type="journal article" year="1992">1992b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D6FF30FB2DEFA38F9FFDCB" author="Ward, P. S. &amp; Brady, S. G. &amp; Fisher, B. L. &amp; Schultz, T. R." box="[1225,1428,502,526]" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" pagination="342 - 362" refId="ref112960" refString="Ward, P. S., Brady, S. G., Fisher, B. L., Schultz, T. R. (2010) Phylogeny and biogeography of dolichoderine ants: Effects of data partitioning and relict taxa on historical inference. Systematic Biology, 59, 342 - 362." type="journal article" year="2010">Ward et al., 2010</bibRefCitation>
) while this and other fossil species currently placed in 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FD1FEC4E89B2FDF6" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[763,953,539,563]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Anonychomyrma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FD1FEC4E89B2FDF6" box="[763,953,539,563]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Anonychomyrma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are well outside this geographic area. The possibility that these species would be better placed in a genus other than 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D6FF30FC2FEC6B8E82FD93" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[971,1161,574,598]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Anonychomyrma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="168" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D6FF30FC2FEC6B8E82FD93" box="[971,1161,574,598]" italics="true" pageId="168" pageNumber="169">Anonychomyrma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, probably newly erected specifically for them, cannot be ruled out.
</paragraph>
